libvaht
------------------------------------------
This is an early version of libvaht, a Mohawk archive and resource reader.
Mohawk is used as the engine of Riven, versions of Myst, and some other
games. Vaht is d'ni for five, as Riven is Gehn's fifth age.

Included, and more useful to most, is vahttool, a command-line Mohawk archive
reader. It reads raw data from all versions of the archive, and will convert
Riven resources to more readable types.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.4.1-1
  libpng16-1.6.20-1
  libvaht-devel-0.3+git20160107-1bl1
  libvaht0-0.3+git20160107-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.21.0-1
  gcc-core-5.3.0-3
  libtool-2.4.6-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/agrif/libvaht

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/agrif/libvaht.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libvaht-0.3+git20160107-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libvaht-0.3+git20160107-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libvaht-0.3+git20160107-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvaht-0.3+git20160107-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvaht0-0.3+git20160107-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libvaht-devel-0.3+git20160107-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

